            <abstract>
                <p>Magic prayer to bind various demons or magicians (among others: <foreign xml:lang="gez">Lebā māš</foreign> - a name, 
                    which may be related to <foreign xml:lang="gez">Lobā</foreign>, which is a name for Satan or to 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">Lebāb</foreign>, which is transcribed from the Arabic term <foreign xml:lang="ar">lubāb</foreign> 
                    meaning "the better one", both of which are mentioned in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres"/>
                    <citedRange unit="page">416</citedRange></bibl>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">Qamañā</foreign> who is a wizard mentioned
                    in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres"/><citedRange unit="page">435</citedRange></bibl>) with the help of the
                    "stone of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾAbenezer</foreign>" which is perhaps related an ancient location in Judea with the name
                    Eben-Ezer, which was mentioned in the Hebrew version of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2697Sam">1 Reg 4:1</ref> (probably
                    also related to <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾAbunāzǝr</foreign>, which was mentioned in 
                    <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1955Prieres"/><citedRange unit="page">452 </citedRange></bibl>, but with another 
                    explanation). Partly written with Amharic terms and irregular orthography.</p>
            </abstract>
